INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `blog_image`, `blog_message`, `posted_at`) VALUES
(1, 'How To Score Above 300 In the 2026 JAMB UTME', 'JAMB News', 'blog_699a30278df034.04184093.jpg', '<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(33,37,41);font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;display:inline !important;float:none;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">If you\'ve been looking for how to score above&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:bolder;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">300&nbsp;</strong></span><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(33,37,41);font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;display:inline !important;float:none;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">in the 2026 JAMB UTME, you\'re in the right place! in this post, candidates will be enlightened on why they need high UTME scores, alongside getting tips and motivational backups for confidence boost in other to achieve this.</span></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">JAMB UTME is one of the most crucial examination where you\'ve to work hard and get yourself prepared for the journey to smashing a high score! Get a low score, and home is always available to receive you for another year. But I\'m sure that\'s not what you want for yourself.</span></p><p><br><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">According to 2023 JAMB statistics, a total of 452,443 candidates applied for medicine whereas only 78,578 MBBS admission slots exist.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">What about Nnamdi Azikiwe University where 2023 candidates admitted to study medicine were less than 200!</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">The same pattern of extremely high demand and limited admission slots for Medicine persisted in the most recent UTME.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">\"Successful people are not gifted; they just work hard, they succeed on purpose\"</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Your aim is to hit a high UTME score and at the end, get admitted into your preferred course of study as you wouldn\'t want to be left behind so, you\'ve to work hard!&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Therefore, if you want to increase your chances of getting admission to the Higher Institution especially into your preferred course of study without any obstacle pulling you back, then a high UTME score is what you have&nbsp;to target.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">2. High JAMB UTME Score Builds Confidence:</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Have you ever felt more confident after achieving a goal? Yes definitely! That\'s also how you feel when you get a high UTME score.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Getting a high UTME score boosts your confidence and makes you perform better in subsequent exams like Post-UTME as well as in school and other aspects of life in general because of the confidence you\'ve worked to build in yourself. So you see, the benefits are all yours!</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">3. Scholarship Opportunities:</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Scoring high in JAMB UTME keeps at a greater chance of being a beneficiary to many Scholarship Awarding Bodies.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Imagine that joy that follows when receiving&nbsp; credit alerts yearly as a student. But you\'ve to work for it, nothing good comes easy! Scoring high in JAMB UTME gives you alot of benefits.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Having seen reasons why you need a high JAMB UTME score, here are incredible tips to guide you if you want to score&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300+&nbsp;</strong>in this forthcoming UTME. Without wasting much time, let\'s get into the tips!</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">1. Get Yourself Together; Eliminate Fear:&nbsp;</strong>\"Never trust your fears, they don\'t know your strength\". - Athena Singh</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">A lot of students after hearing the word \"JAMB\" or \"UTME\" become gripped with fear, never knowing that\'s the beginning of their failure.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">JAMB UTME is forthcoming, and it\'s known as of the exam students dread the most in Nigeria but are you going to limit your academic growth or refuse to further because you are afraid of an exam? Definitely No! Deep inside, you are willing to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;but there\'s no way you can achieve this if you don\'t believe in yourself.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Here are tips on how to get rid of low self-esteem and build confidence in studies:</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓&nbsp;</strong>Believe and say to yourself; \"I can do it\"</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓ Make something your motivation:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;This is one of the best way to improve in yourself. Your parents, your future ambition etc can be your motivation.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">That moment when you start losing confidence in yourself, just remember what your motivation is and be like; \" I have to make mama proud\", \"I remember I want to be a doctor\", I would like to be a famous engineer\" and all that. You can jo</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Remembering your motivation keeps you focused on your goal and put you back on track when deviating.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓ Never settle for less:&nbsp;</strong>Avoid that thought of getting scores like&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">200 or 220.&nbsp;</strong>Say to yourself; \"Scoring 200 is is easy but I\'m not settling for that, my target is to score&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>and above and with hardwork and God\'s help, I believe I can do it\". You\'ve to motivate yourself in order to achieve your goals and bring the best out of yourself.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">2 . PLAN:&nbsp;</strong>The second factor to consider when aiming to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>is to&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">PLAN.</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">After you must have eliminated all forms of fear and putting yourself together, Planning on how to achieve this goal of scoring above 300 is what follows.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">We\'re all conversant with the popular saying; \"Failing to plan means planning to fail\". Therefore these are things to consider when making out your&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">study plans.</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓ Study Pattern:&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">A lot of students today, just jump into reading without choosing the right study pattern that suits them and at the end of the day, achieving little or nothing.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Therefore, choosing the right pattern of studies when studying for JAMB UTME makes reading more easier and efficient and helps you cover a lot during study hours. So when planning to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>in JAMB UTME, your study plan can be in the following format;</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">• Reading two subjects daily,&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">• Solving &amp; studying two different years of the JAMB Past questions and answers, daily, etc</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">You know yourself better than I do , so create a study guide and pattern that fits you the most and ensure you stick to it until the last day to your exam.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">3. Increase Study Duration And Remove Distractions:&nbsp;</strong>Now that you\'ve created&nbsp; a study pattern to guide you, the next thing to do is to increase study duration.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Come on, your aim is to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300</strong>! Nothing less. To achieve this, you\'ve to increase the time to which you give to your studies. Scoring above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>in JAMB UTME means that you\'ve known&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">75%&nbsp;</strong>and above of your study materials and there\'s no way you can achieve this if you give just little time to studies.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Therefore, as a student intending to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300,&nbsp;</strong>your minimum study duration should be&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">6 hours daily.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;Yes! There\'s alot of things to cover so you can go above 6 hours if you can but it shouldn\'t be less than 6 hours unless you want a lower score, which I\'m sure that\'s not what you want.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">4 Get Rid Of Distractions:&nbsp;</strong>This is one of the most difficult task for many students, it\'s just like an addiction. You don\'t have a choice! You should have to let go of what would distracts you when studying.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">To remain focused on studies especially when intending to score&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>and above, then you\'ve to remove all forms of distractions like your Phone, Television and anything you know would deviate your mind during studies.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">When I was preparing for for my UTME, I said to myself; \"It\'s better I suffer myself reading for the next two to three months to my exams than suffer again for another year if I fail to pass\" and that mentality helped me a lot.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">I had to delete my Facebook App, Movies, Video games and any other thing that could have distracted me and after my exams, I started using them again until I got tired. What was in my phone when I was studying for JAMB UTME was just some Textbooks in PDF, WhatsApp, and Myschool App which I used in practicing CBT Past Questions and Answers.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">You can do same too. I advise you even smash your phone and throw inside the River. (Just joking tho😊)&nbsp; but what I\'m trying to put across is that you should learn how to minimize distractions during study hours. You can do it. It just requires discipline!</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">5. Work On Efficiency During Studies And Jot While Reading</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Studying efficiently helps you cover alot and makes you retain information and ideas for a long period of time.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Efficiency during studies can be achieved by;</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓&nbsp;Having A Baseline Knowledge</strong>: You can do this by watching a video Tutorial on the topic you are about to read. Doing this, understanding the topic about to be read becomes more easier during studies.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓ Begin Your Day With Reading:&nbsp;</strong>This must not be for hours but once you wake up early each day; say your morning prayers, then go ahead to read something. This keeps your mind refreshed and makes you active during the remaining study periods of the day. Cultivating this habit improves study efficiency and reminds you of your goal.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">✓ Jot While Reading (very important):&nbsp;</strong>One of the most efficient way to study especially when aiming to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>in JAMB UTME, is&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">Jotting.</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Jotting while reading helps you pen down important information from your Textbooks and study materials. Therefore anytime you feel you are forgetting something, you just run to your jotter, and pick the information rather than going back to the Textbook to look for the page again.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Finally, jotting while studying for JAMB UTME makes revision more easy and helps you recall information and ideas better. During free period and after studies, it\'s advisable to go through your jotter.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">6. Avoid Skipping Of Topics And Overcome Your Weak Areas</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">No matter how well&nbsp; you try to study a subject, there are some topics you tend to find&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">boring&nbsp;</strong>and will want to skip them. Please don\'t do that! Your aim is to score above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>right? Then you\'ve to stop skipping topics. Instead, give more time to them.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Let me ask you a question. Let\'s say you skip a particular area because you lack enthusiasm for that topic and the day of your exam, a question comes out from there. What will you do, skip the question too?</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Definitely No! Now you see more reasons why you\'ve to carry every topic on your JAMB Syllables along because JAMB don\'t care if you\'ve read a topic or not! They can set question from anywhere and you wouldn\'t want to score less than 300 right? Then you\'ve to avoid skipping of topics you find boring and give more time, work on your weak areas and carry your strength along too.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">7. Study And Solve A Lot Of JAMB UTME Past Questions And Answers</strong></span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">JAMB Past Questions contains questions from topics you\'ve read, topic you\'ve just read, and topics which you are going to read in subsequent time. Solving and understanding past questions keeps you refreshed and check your success level at the course of studying.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Finally, solving a lot of JAMB Past Questions And Answers gives you bonus points on the day of your exam if you\'re lucky to come across repeated questions.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">To study smart, you need to practice with the &nbsp;</span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(2, 117, 216);outline:none;text-decoration:none;touch-action:manipulation;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://myschool.ng/latest-jamb-cbt-practice-mobile-app-free-download\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Myschool&nbsp;JAMB CBT Mobile App</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;for android phones or the&nbsp;</span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(2, 117, 216);outline:none;text-decoration:none;touch-action:manipulation;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://myschool.ng/latest-jamb-cbt-practice-software-free-download\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Myschool&nbsp;JAMB CBT Software</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;for Computer systems. Both contain over 60,000 JAMB past questions&nbsp;and answers.&nbsp;You can equally check out the&nbsp;</span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(2, 117, 216);outline:none;text-decoration:none;touch-action:manipulation;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://myschool.ng/classroom\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Myschool CBT Classroom</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">. You should also join our</span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(2, 117, 216);outline:none;text-decoration:none;touch-action:manipulation;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://myschool.ng/jamb-whatsapp-group\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"> JAMB WhatsApp group</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"> to get instant advice and answers to your questions. </span><a style=\"background-color:transparent;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(2, 117, 216);outline:none;text-decoration:none;touch-action:manipulation;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://myschool.ng/jamb-whatsapp-group\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Join here</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">8. Always Memorize:&nbsp;</strong>Have you ever wondered why you tend to forget what you\'ve read after sometime? Well it\'s because you don\'t memorize.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Learning how to memorize after studies boost and improves your ability to retain those information and ideas for a long period of time. This can be done during your free time, when washing clothes or doing other house chores. It\'s going to be fun. Believe me.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">9. Stay Healthy:&nbsp;</strong>Keeping yourself healthy and in the right frame of mind helps you to be stronger and ready for the journey to scoring above&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">300&nbsp;</strong>​​​​​​in JAMB. Not ONLY JAMB, but other aspects of life too.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Therefore; feed well, give yourself good sleep and take short break during study hours and do what you enjoy during the break.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Lastly,</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;font-weight:bolder;\">10. Prayers:&nbsp;</strong>We\'ve to involve God in all we do. So ask God for directions, guidance, good health and excellent result after your exam.</span></p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(33, 37, 41);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:justify;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">To this, we\'ve come to the end of this post, congratulations to you all that made it here. Ensure you follow the tips and stick to them until the last day to your exam .</span></p>', '2026-02-21 22:22:31');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `blog_image`, `blog_message`, `posted_at`) VALUES
(2, 'WAEC releases 2025 private WASSCE results, female candidates outperform males', 'WAEC News', 'blog_699a39d1b8c910.33464762.jpg', '<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">The West African Examinations Council has announced the release of results for the 2025 Second Series of the Computer-Based West African Senior School Certificate Examination for private candidates, with performance declining by 11.47 percentage points compared to 2024.</p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">The release was contained in a statement issued Monday night by WAEC’s Head of Public Affairs, Moyosola Adesina.</p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">According to the council, 42.17 per cent of candidates obtained credit passes in at least five subjects, including English Language and Mathematics.</p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">This represents a drop from the 53.64 per cent recorded in 2024. In 2023, 44.29 per cent of candidates achieved the same benchmark.</p><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:735/375;\" src=\"/school_app/uploads/blogs/blog_img_699a39b62746d2.24470306.jpg\" width=\"735\" height=\"375\"></figure><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">The result analysis further showed that 33,989 candidates, representing 51.69 per cent, obtained credit passes in at least five subjects, with or without English Language and Mathematics.</p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">A total of 69,604 candidates registered for the examination, reflecting a 1.8 per cent increase from the 68,342 who enrolled in 2024. Of this number, 65,752 candidates sat the examination at 370 centres nationwide.</p><p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 51);font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;;font-size:17px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26.35px;margin-bottom:1rem;margin-top:0px;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">The council disclosed that 61,943 candidates, representing 94.21 per cent of those who sat the examination, have had their results fully processed and released.</p>', '2026-02-21 23:03:45'),
